  "prompt": "If he's over me then why does he send me random messages and pictures?",
  "response": "There could be several reasons why he sends you random messages and pictures even if he claims to be over you. Here are a few possibilities:\n\n1. **Mixed Feelings**: He might still have feelings for you but is confused about them. Sending messages could be his way of keeping a connection alive.\n\n2. **Friendship Attempt**: He might want to maintain a friendship and feels comfortable sending you messages and pictures, viewing you as a friend rather than a romantic partner.\n\n3. **Nostalgia**: He could be reminiscing about the times you shared and is sending messages as a way to relive those moments.\n\n4. **Boredom or Loneliness**: Sometimes, people reach out to ex-partners when they\u2019re feeling lonely or bored, without necessarily wanting to rekindle a romantic relationship.\n\n5. **Testing the Waters**: He may be testing whether you\u2019re still interested or available, possibly hoping to gauge your reaction.\n\n6. **Attention Seeking**: He might enjoy the attention or validation he gets from interacting with you, even if he claims to have moved on.\n\nUltimately, the best way to understand his motivations is to communicate openly about how you both feel.",
